<thead>
<tr>
<th>en</th>
<th>gloss</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>I walk <b>on</b> the street</td>
<td><span class="gloss">me</span> <span class="gloss">do</span> <span class="gloss">go-arm-go</span> <span class="gloss-emph">surface</span> <span class="gloss">go-way</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>I talk to him <b>out of</b> necessity</td>
<td><span class="gloss">me</span> <span class="gloss">talk</span> <span class="gloss">this</span> <span class="gloss-emph">reason</span> <span class="gloss">big-want</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>I lived here <b>for</b> three years</td>
<td><span class="gloss">me</span> <span class="gloss">back</span> <span class="gloss">life</span> <span class="gloss">this-place</span> <span class="gloss">three</span> <span class="gloss">big-dirt-time</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>I love him <b>for</b> his smile</td>
<td><span class="gloss">me</span> <span class="gloss">do</span> <span class="gloss">love</span> <span class="gloss">this</span> <span class="gloss-emph">reason</span> <span class="gloss">good-energy-head-front</span> <span class="gloss">of</span> <span class="gloss">this</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>I fight <b>for</b> my country</td>
<td><span class="gloss">me</span> <span class="gloss">do</span> <span class="gloss">against</span> <span class="gloss-emph">reason</span> <span class="gloss">law-place</span> <span class="gloss">of</span> <span class="gloss">me</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>I <b> for gay</b> marriage</td>
<td><span class="gloss">me</span> <span class="gloss-emph">do</span> <span class="gloss-emph">over-energy</span> <span class="gloss">one-kind-love</span> <span class="gloss">law-love</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>



At this point, you already know most of the language’s grammar!


